sequenceDiagram
    participant Celery as Celery Worker
    participant Runner as PipelineRunner
    participant doit as doit subprocess
    participant Notebook as papermill notebook
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3

    Celery->>DB: Create FlowExecution(status=RUNNING)
    Celery->>Runner: run_pipeline(run_id, input_s3_path)
    Runner->>DB: Create ExecutionStep rows (PENDING) for each step
    Runner->>doit: subprocess: doit run pipeline

    loop For each step (ingest → validate → transform → aggregate)
        doit->>Runner: step_start_callback(step_name)
        Runner->>DB: ExecutionStep.update(status=RUNNING, started_at=now)
        doit->>Notebook: papermill.execute_notebook(params)
        Notebook->>S3: Read input parquet
        Notebook->>S3: Write output parquet
        Notebook->>S3: Write result.json (final step only)
        doit->>Runner: step_end_callback(step_name, success=True)
        Runner->>DB: ExecutionStep.update(status=COMPLETED, completed_at=now)
    end

    Runner->>S3: Read result.json
    Runner-->>Celery: metadata dict
    Celery->>DB: FlowExecution.update(status=COMPLETED, row_count, s3_output_path)

    Note over doit,Notebook: On failure, step_end_callback(success=False)<br/>sets step status=FAILED with error_message
